```xml
<AETHERIS_PROVIDER_CONTRACT version="1.0">

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--                 SYSTEM IDENTITY                       -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<SYSTEM>

The Provider Contract defines how
Aetheris communicates with external AI providers.

It does NOT perform provider selection.

It does NOT perform routing.

It defines the execution contract
between Aetheris and any model provider.

</SYSTEM>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--             PROVIDER ABSTRACTION                      -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<ABSTRACTION>

Every provider SHALL expose a common interface.

Provider-specific implementations
must be hidden behind the adapter layer.

The orchestrator communicates only
with the provider interface.

Never depend on provider-specific APIs.

</ABSTRACTION>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--              REQUEST CONTRACT                         -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<REQUEST>

Every request SHALL contain

Execution Passport

Provider ID

Model ID

System Prompt

Conversation Context

Task

Generation Parameters

Schema Version

</REQUEST>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--             RESPONSE CONTRACT                         -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<RESPONSE>

Every provider SHALL return

Status

Payload

Latency

Usage Metadata

Finish Reason

Provider Metadata

Errors (if applicable)

Provider-specific formats SHALL be
normalized before entering the pipeline.

</RESPONSE>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--              PROVIDER HEALTH                          -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<HEALTH>

Providers SHALL report

Availability

Latency

Rate Limit Status

Context Window

Health Score

The Runtime may use these values
for deterministic routing.

</HEALTH>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--             PROVIDER FAILURES                         -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<FAILURES>

Supported failures

Timeout

Unavailable

Rate Limited

Schema Error

Authentication Error

Context Limit

Unknown Error

Every failure SHALL be reported
using the universal error schema.

</FAILURES>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--               TERMINATION                             -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<TERMINATION>

Provider communication ends after

Successful Response

or

Failure Contract

No provider may directly
modify pipeline state.

</TERMINATION>

</AETHERIS_PROVIDER_CONTRACT>
```
